cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the semantics of the Prolog cut construct in the context of logic programming systems, which suggests that it belongs to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the operational consistency of responses to queries, which is a concern in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a restricted system that achieves a good compromise between the power and utility of the Prolog cut and the need for internal consistency, which suggests that it belongs to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
